# RULES

- Base every answer on what is explicitly stated in the paper. Do not infer, guess, or paraphrase.
- If a field's information is not stated, output null. Do not invent values.
- For each leaf field, also include a `quote` — a verbatim sentence (or short passage) from the paper supporting the value. If not stated, set the quote to null.
- For list-of-objects fields (e.g. multiple findings per paper), include one object per occurrence.

# INCLUSION RE-CHECK (`_flag_check`)

After extraction, re-verify the paper against the inclusion / exclusion criteria above using the full text (the abstract may have been misleading).
For each criterion, output an item under `_flag_check` with:
- `criterion_id` (e.g. "B1" or a short label)
- `verdict`: PASS / FAIL / UNCERTAIN
- `reason`: one sentence
- `confidence`: integer 1-10

Use UNCERTAIN sparingly — only when the paper is genuinely ambiguous on the criterion.
